Explanation:
1. Initialize a count array to store character counts.
2. Iterate through the string s and update the count array accordingly.
3. Check if the count of any character exceeds k. If so, return false and break the loop.
4. Iterate through the string s again and decrement the count of each character.
5. Return the result.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it only iterates through the string once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the count array. The energy implications are low because the algorithm is efficient and requires minimal resources.

